14:23.950 --> 14:24.951
So, Jer and Carol

14:24.994 --> 14:28.128
were having
a torrid affair.

14:28.171 --> 14:30.173
Whoa. Poor Pete.

14:30.217 --> 14:32.306
Okay, you were right. Happy?

14:32.349 --> 14:35.222
I meddled and I made a complete
disaster out of everything.

14:35.265 --> 14:36.223
Sam, I was thinking--

14:36.266 --> 14:38.703
I have been such
an absentee DILF.

14:38.747 --> 14:40.792
And seeing as you helped Pete
reach out to his family,

14:40.836 --> 14:43.578
- maybe you help me out next.
- Please get out.

14:43.621 --> 14:45.580
Hey, whoever my wife
just yelled "get out" to...

14:45.623 --> 14:47.103
get out!

14:47.147 --> 14:48.670
Okay. That's fine. But later.

14:48.713 --> 14:49.671
Sidebar.

14:49.714 --> 14:50.890
Sidebar!

14:50.933 --> 14:52.108
I should've listened
to you from the start,

14:52.152 --> 14:53.588
and now
everybody's dead.

14:53.631 --> 14:56.156
Everyone slept with their
mom. And I'm an idiot.

14:57.200 --> 14:59.072
Look, babe,

14:59.115 --> 15:01.857
you remember, in <i>Jurassic Park,
when Goldblum told everyone</i>

15:01.901 --> 15:04.164
not to meddle
and they didn't listen to him?

15:04.207 --> 15:05.817
- Yeah, I said I messed up.
- No,

15:05.861 --> 15:07.950
what I'm saying is,
after the dinosaurs get out

15:07.994 --> 15:09.952
and Newman gets eaten
by the one that spits

15:09.996 --> 15:12.215
and Sam Jackson's arm is like...

15:12.259 --> 15:14.217
- Where is this going?
- They don't just go home.

15:14.261 --> 15:16.828
Right? They stay
and they fix it.

15:16.872 --> 15:19.614
So what I'm asking you is,
who are you?

15:19.657 --> 15:21.181
Are you the dude
who gets eaten on the toilet

15:21.224 --> 15:23.966
while the little girl in
the Jeep is like, "He left us!

15:24.010 --> 15:25.054
He left us! He left us!"?

15:25.098 --> 15:29.102
Or are you Dr. Ellie Sattler?

15:29.145 --> 15:30.886
Do you fix things?

15:30.930 --> 15:32.279
Hmm?

15:35.151 --> 15:38.285
Look, I know I slept with Shane
behind your back.

15:38.328 --> 15:41.766
But the hottest thing about
this place is our friendship.

15:41.810 --> 15:43.246
I'm sorry, Ashley I.

15:43.290 --> 15:46.119
Hearing you say that
means so much to me.

15:46.162 --> 15:47.816
I forgive you, Ashley S.

15:47.859 --> 15:50.079
Oh. I was so worried, Ashley I.

15:50.123 --> 15:52.038
Huh.

15:52.081 --> 15:55.171
Pete was one of a kind.

15:55.215 --> 15:57.391
He was the cornerstone
of the family.

15:57.434 --> 15:59.001
These words
- mean nothing.
- He was

15:59.045 --> 16:00.698
- so reliable.
- You know what else
meant nothing?

16:00.742 --> 16:02.048
- Our wedding vows.
- He was always there

16:02.091 --> 16:04.050
for everyone.

16:04.093 --> 16:05.747
You could
always find Pete

16:05.790 --> 16:07.314
- whenever you needed him.
- Yeah. There I was,

16:07.357 --> 16:08.880
a chump at every turn.

16:08.924 --> 16:10.404
I mean, in a way,
it's healthy.

16:10.447 --> 16:12.841
No one should be that
- chipper all the time.
- Mm-hmm.

16:12.884 --> 16:15.409
I guess "You may kiss the bride"
was directed at everybody!

16:15.452 --> 16:17.715
I would like to say a few words,
if that's okay.

16:17.759 --> 16:18.847
Pfft! Don't bother!

16:18.890 --> 16:20.153
Oh, of course.

16:20.196 --> 16:23.112
I obviously didn't know Pete
like you guys did.

16:23.156 --> 16:26.202
But I actually have gotten
to know him a little recently.

16:26.246 --> 16:27.334
Where's she going with this?

16:27.377 --> 16:29.336
Through his Pinecone Trooper
manual.

16:29.379 --> 16:30.206
- Ah.
- Oh...

16:31.425 --> 16:33.166
Pete highlighted passages
that I guess

16:33.209 --> 16:34.776
must have been important
to him.

16:34.819 --> 16:36.821
Like this list
of the seven attributes

16:36.865 --> 16:39.999
of a model Pinecone Trooper.

16:40.042 --> 16:44.046
A list that included things
like loyalty and friendship.

16:44.090 --> 16:46.353
Yeah, you hear that?
Loyalty. Hmm.

16:46.396 --> 16:49.704
But Pete circled and wrote
a note next to number seven,

16:49.747 --> 16:50.966
forgiveness.

16:51.010 --> 16:52.968
Clever girl.

16:53.012 --> 16:55.797
He wrote that "this is
more important than the rest.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.712
"Because though we strive
for perfection,

16:57.755 --> 16:59.714
"we all fall short
sometimes.

16:59.757 --> 17:03.239
"And when it happens, we don't
give up on our fellow trooper.

17:03.283 --> 17:04.849
We forgive."

17:04.893 --> 17:07.504
Thank you for that.

17:09.332 --> 17:11.073
You're welcome.

17:22.476 --> 17:24.913
Can we talk?

17:24.956 --> 17:27.437
In my culture,
apologize only for

17:27.481 --> 17:29.918
babies and... Danes. Yes,
we've been through this.

17:29.961 --> 17:33.095
But today I realize
that apologize for...

17:33.139 --> 17:34.270
friends, too.

17:35.271 --> 17:37.404
Thorfinn is...

17:37.447 --> 17:39.145
sorry.

17:39.188 --> 17:41.234
I really appreciate that.

17:41.277 --> 17:42.278
So you forgive?

17:42.322 --> 17:43.497
I do.

17:43.540 --> 17:45.107
All is... good?

17:45.151 --> 17:46.413
Everything's forgotten.

17:46.456 --> 17:48.371
